{"title": "Glories of Mary", "description": "The Glories of Mary is a classic book in the field of Roman Catholic Mariology, written during the 18th century by Saint Alphonsus Liguori, a Doctor of the Church.<br />\nThe book was written at a time when some Jansenists (which were declared heretical by the Pope) were criticizing Marian devotions, and was written in part as a defense of Marian devotion. The book combines numerous citations in favor of devotion to the Blessed Virgin Mary from the Church Fathers and the Doctors of the Church with Saint Alphonsus' own personal views on Marian veneration and includes a number of Marian prayers and practices. - Summary by Wikipedia", "duration": 68485, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "10334", "name": "Saint Alphonsus Liguori"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt33/gloriesofmary_1407.jpg", "copyright_year": "1888", "genres": ["Christianity - Other"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Maria Therese"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/glories_of_mary_amb_1407_librivox/gloriesofmary_00_liguori_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1041}, {"section": 1, "title": "Part I Chapter I Section 1", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/glories_of_mary_amb_1407_librivox/gloriesofmary_01_liguori_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1210}, {"section": 2, "title": "Part I Chapter I Section 2", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/glories_of_mary_amb_1407_librivox/gloriesofmary_02_liguori_64kb.mp3", "duration": 969}, {"section": 3, "title": "Part I Chapter I Section 3", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/glories_of_mary_amb_1407_librivox/gloriesofmary_03_liguori_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1529}, {"section": 4, "title": "